The thump of airplane wheels on asphalt jolted me from my sleep.

LineNo: 14278025,

Narrator: I was seated in the commercial jet...
en


I was seated in the commercial jet we'd chartered for our royal visit to Thornbough. It had been a long, bumpy ride.

LineNo: 14278127,

Narrator: As we descended the airplane stairs...
en


As we descended the airplane stairs onto the tarmac, a horn quartet played a jubilant fanfare. Photographers in a cordoned-off press area eagerly began snapping pictures.

LineNo: 14278229,

Narrator: A red carpet stretched from the pla...
en


A red carpet stretched from the plane to a waiting motorcade. Next to a pair of limousines, Beatrice Livingston and the Rumburg royal family waited to greet us.

LineNo: 14278331,

Narrator: The Queen regarded me politely, but...
en


The Queen regarded me politely, but with some remove. She held out her hand.

LineNo: 14279005,

Player_Romus_Italic: I kissed my sister-in-law's hand. S...
en


I kissed my sister-in-law's hand. She gave a prim smile of approval.

LineNo: 14279011,

Player_Romus_Italic: I kissed my sister-in-law's hand. S...
Menu Text en


Kiss it.

LineNo: 14279113,

Player_Romus_Italic: I shook my sister-in-law's hand. Sh...
en


I shook my sister-in-law's hand. She rapidly withdrew it.

LineNo: 14279119,

Player_Romus_Italic: I shook my sister-in-law's hand. Sh...
Menu Text en


Shake it.

LineNo: 14279221,

en


I attempted to embrace my sister-in-law. She politely pulled away.

LineNo: 14279227,

Player_Romus_Italic: I attempted to embrace my sister-in...
Menu Text en


Give her a hug.

LineNo: 14279329,

Narrator: The queen's eyes brimmed with sympa...
en


The queen's eyes brimmed with sympathy as I approached. She pulled me into an embrace.

LineNo: 14279431,

Narrator: The queen had a compassionate look...
en


The queen had a compassionate look in her eyes as I approached. We exchanged cheek kisses.

LineNo: 14279533,

Beatrice Livingston (R): My dear, dear brother-in-law. You'...
en


"My dear, dear brother-in-law. You've gotten yourself into quite the mess, haven't you?"

Player_Romus: Nothing Rumburg can't get me out o...
en


"Nothing Rumburg can't get me out of."

LineNo: 14279761,

Beatrice Livingston (R): My dear brother-in-law. What a ple...
en


"My dear brother-in-law. What a pleasure it is to finally host you in Thornbourgh."

LineNo: 14279879,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Romus, Your Majesty. You've gotten...
en


"Romus, Your Majesty. You've gotten yourself into quite the mess."

en


"Romus, Your Majesty. It has been some time."

LineNo: 14280131,

Player_Romus: Nonsense. Everything in Pales is p...
en


"Nonsense. Everything in Pales is perfectly under control."

LineNo: 14280233,

Player_Romus: It's almost a good thing your sist...
en


"It's almost a good thing your sister didn't live to see these times."

LineNo: 14280605,

Player_Romus: 'Mess' is an understatement.
en


"'Mess' is an understatement."

LineNo: 14280707,

Narrator: She stepped back with a scandalized...
en


She stepped back with a scandalized look on her face.

LineNo: 14280809,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Yes, well, fear not.
en


"Yes, well, fear not."

LineNo: 14280911,

Beatrice Livingston (R): That is the idea.
en


"That is the idea."

LineNo: 14281013,

Beatrice Livingston (R): It will only be under control once...
en


"It will only be under control once you have won."

LineNo: 14281115,

Player_Romus: I'm looking forward to your legend...
en


"I'm looking forward to your legendary Rumburgian hospitality."

LineNo: 14281217,

Player_Romus: Your niece sends her warmest wishe...
en


"Your niece sends her warmest wishes."

LineNo: 14281597,

Player_Romus: Nothing Rumburg can't get me out o...
en


"Nothing Rumburg can't get me out of."

LineNo: 14281699,

Player_Romus: Nonsense. Everything in Pales is p...
en


"Nonsense. Everything in Pales is perfectly under control."

LineNo: 14281801,

Player_Romus: It's almost a good thing your sist...
en


"It's almost a good thing your sister didn't live to see these times. Almost."

LineNo: 14281903,

Player_Romus: It's not a mess. It's a catastroph...
en


"It's not a mess. It's a catastrophe."

LineNo: 14282005,

Narrator: She stepped back with a horrified l...
en


She stepped back with a horrified look on her face.

LineNo: 14282107,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I was speaking euphemistically. It...
en


"I was speaking euphemistically. It's the Rumburgian way."

LineNo: 14282209,

Beatrice Livingston (R): We will see about that.
en


"We will see about that."

LineNo: 14282311,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I was not only speaking about Pale...
en


"I was not only speaking about Pales."

LineNo: 14282683,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Please refrain from such attempts...
en


"Please refrain from such attempts at 'comedy'."

LineNo: 14282785,

Player_Romus: Indeed, Your Excellency. How have...
en


"Indeed, Your Excellency. How have you been?"

LineNo: 14282887,

Player_Romus: Really? I feel like I just saw you.
en


"Really? I feel like I just saw you."

LineNo: 14283267,

Player_Romus: An eternity, and yet no time at al...
en


"An eternity, and yet no time at all."

LineNo: 14283369,

Player_Romus: Your niece sends her warmest wishe...
en


"Your niece sends her warmest wishes."

LineNo: 14283471,

Player_Romus: I know we've drifted apart over th...
en


"I know we've drifted apart over the past years, but it's a pleasure to be here."

LineNo: 14283573,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Drifted apart. Yes.
en


"Drifted apart. Yes."

LineNo: 14283675,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I have been better. As have you.
en


"I have been better. As have you."

LineNo: 14283777,

Beatrice Livingston (R): A pity she could not be here.
en


"A pity she could not be here."

LineNo: 14284157,

Beatrice Livingston (R): How lovely. I'm just dying to hear...
en


"How lovely. I'm just dying to hear about her time in the Grand Duchy."

LineNo: 14284259,

Beatrice Livingston (R): How lovely. A pity she could not b...
en


"How lovely. A pity she could not be here."

LineNo: 14284361,

Player_Romus: We'll have to make this a quick vi...
en


"We'll have to make this a quick visit, I'm afraid. Turbulent times back home."

LineNo: 14284463,

Beatrice Livingston (R): You will not be disappointed. Eith...
en


"You will not be disappointed. Either of you."

LineNo: 14284565,

Narrator: She raised an eyebrow.
en


She raised an eyebrow.

LineNo: 14284945,

Beatrice Livingston (R): So I hear.
en


"So I hear."

LineNo: 14285047,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Really? From where I'm sitting, yo...
en


"Really? From where I'm sitting, your reign looks smooth as silk."

LineNo: 14285149,

Beatrice Livingston (R): If that was a joke, it's not very...
en


"If that was a joke, it's not very amusing."

LineNo: 14285251,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Surely you are being facetious. So...
en


"Surely you are being facetious. So much has changed."

LineNo: 14285353,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Hrm, yes. Poetic.
en


"Hrm, yes. Poetic."

LineNo: 14285733,

Narrator: I had just finished getting dressed...
en


I had just finished getting dressed when Lucita entered the compartment. She was outfitted in full military regalia.

LineNo: 14286137,

Narrator: I was in the bedroom of my royal je...
en


I was in the bedroom of my royal jet, {RiziaDLCText.RoyalJet}. It had been a long but smooth flight to Thornbourgh.

LineNo: 14286517,

Narrator: I had just finished getting dressed...
en


I had just finished getting dressed when I heard a knock on the door to my compartment.

LineNo: 14286619,

Player_Romus: I love a woman in uniform.
en


"I love a woman in uniform."

LineNo: 14286721,

Narrator: I had just finished getting dressed...
en


I had just finished getting dressed when I heard a knock on the door to my compartment.

LineNo: 14286823,

en


"Your Majesty? Are you decent?"

LineNo: 14286949,

Lucita Azaro: Your Majesty? Are you decent?
en


"Your Majesty? Are you decent?"

LineNo: 14287075,

Player_Romus: Decent, no. Dressed, yes.
en


"Decent, no. Dressed, yes."

LineNo: 14287447,

Player_Romus: What is it?
en


"What is it?"

LineNo: 14287549,

Player_Romus: You may enter.
en


"You may enter."

LineNo: 14287651,

Player_Romus: Ready to meet my sister-in-law?
en


"Ready to meet my sister-in-law?"

LineNo: 14287753,

Player_Romus: How dare you barge in on me like t...
en


"How dare you barge in on me like that? I could've been naked."

LineNo: 14287855,

Player_Romus: You can't see it, but I'm saluting...
en


"You can't see it, but I'm saluting you right now."

LineNo: 14288227,

Narrator: She bowed in faux humility.
en


She bowed in faux humility.

LineNo: 14288329,

Narrator: She grimaced.
en


She grimaced.

LineNo: 14288431,

Lucita Azaro: It's been more than a decade. You...
en


"It's been more than a decade. You are in-laws no longer."

LineNo: 14288533,

Narrator: She flashed me a grin.
en


She flashed me a grin.

LineNo: 14288635,

Lucita Azaro: At your service, Your Majesty.
en


"At your service, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 14288737,

Lucita Azaro: Apologies, Your Majesty. Next time...
en


"Apologies, Your Majesty. Next time I'll barge in earlier."

LineNo: 14288839,

Player_Romus: I have always tried my hardest to...
en


"I have always tried my hardest to be a decent man and a decent king."

LineNo: 14288941,

Narrator: With a smile, she entered.
en


With a smile, she entered.

LineNo: 14289043,

Narrator: She sat next to me on the bed and s...
en


She sat next to me on the bed and squeezed my hand.

LineNo: 14289145,

Lucita Azaro: I hope the Queen's in a good mood....
en


"I hope the Queen's in a good mood. Rumburg's support could really turn the tide against Pales."

LineNo: 14289557,

Narrator: With a smile, he entered.
en


With a smile, he entered.

LineNo: 14289937,

Narrator: She came in and bowed.
en


She came in and bowed.

LineNo: 14290039,

Narrator: He came in and bowed.
en


He came in and bowed.

LineNo: 14290141,

Narrator: Lucita was in the seat next to mine...
en


Lucita was in the seat next to mine. On seeing I was awake, she squeezed my hand surreptitiously.

LineNo: 14290799,

Narrator: Lucita was in the seat next to mine...
en


Lucita was in the seat next to mine. On seeing I was awake, she smiled.

LineNo: 14290901,

Narrator: Laurento was in the seat next to mi...
en


Laurento was in the seat next to mine. On seeing I was awake, he smiled.

LineNo: 14291003,

Lucita Azaro: Good morning, Your Majesty. I'm gl...
en


"Good morning, Your Majesty. I'm glad you were able to get some rest."

LineNo: 14291129,

Laurento Esquibel: Good morning, Your Majesty. I'm gl...
en


"Good morning, Your Majesty. I'm glad you were able to get some rest."

LineNo: 14291255,

Player_Romus: Are you joking? I can hardly sleep...
en


"Are you joking? I can hardly sleep in my own bed, let alone on an airplane."

LineNo: 14291357,

Player_Romus: I always sleep well on airplanes....
en


"I always sleep well on airplanes. No phone calls or letters, no responsibilities except to get from point A to point B."

LineNo: 14291459,

Player_Romus: It wasn't easy. I've been nervous...
en


"It wasn't easy. I've been nervous about today's meeting."

LineNo: 14291561,

Player_Romus: I was having the most marvelous dr...
en


"I was having the most marvelous dream. I think you were involved."

LineNo: 14291941,

Laurento Esquibel: Really? That's quite the honor.
en


"Really? That's quite the honor."

LineNo: 14292043,

Lucita Azaro: How fascinating. I suggest we unpa...
en


"How fascinating. I suggest we unpack its meaning in private later."

LineNo: 14292423,

Lucita Azaro: What an honor, Your Majesty. I ass...
en


"What an honor, Your Majesty. I assume I was clothed."

LineNo: 14292525,

Laurento Esquibel: Ah. Your father was the same way....
en


"Ah. Your father was the same way. Restless till the end."

LineNo: 14292905,

Lucita Azaro: Sorry to hear. I've trained myself...
en


"Sorry to hear. I've trained myself to be able to sleep on any surface."

LineNo: 14293285,

Lucita Azaro: Your military training didn't take...
en


"Your military training didn't take, then. They taught me to be able to sleep anywhere."

LineNo: 14293665,

Laurento Esquibel: Refreshing, I agree.
en


"Refreshing, I agree."

LineNo: 14294045,

Laurento Esquibel: Understandably so.
en


"Understandably so."

LineNo: 14294147,

Lucita Azaro: Very understandable.
en


"Very understandable."

LineNo: 14294249,

Narrator: She adjusted the pins over her brea...
en


She adjusted the pins over her breast pocket.

LineNo: 14294351,

Narrator: He pulled a tin of wax out of his p...
en


He pulled a tin of wax out of his pocket and dabbed some onto the ends of his moustache.

LineNo: 14294453,

Lucita Azaro: And plan for what will happen once...
en


"And plan for what will happen once we land."

LineNo: 14294555,

Lucita Azaro: Just making sure you're ready for...
en


"Just making sure you're ready for our meeting with your sister-in-law."

LineNo: 14294657,

Laurento Esquibel: Just making sure you're ready for...
en


"Just making sure you're ready for our meeting with your sister-in-law."

LineNo: 14294759,

Laurento Esquibel: Rumburg's foreign ministers have h...
en


"Rumburg's foreign ministers have hinted that the Queen is quite dissatisfied with our recent actions."

LineNo: 14295155,

Laurento Esquibel: With all the foreign turmoil happe...
en


"With all the foreign turmoil happening lately, it is comforting to know that Queen Beatrice is still on our side."

LineNo: 14295551,

Player_Romus: I doubt it. I've done nothing but...
en


"I doubt it. I've done nothing but alienate Rumburg since my coronation."

LineNo: 14295653,

Player_Romus: She had better be. I've been bendi...
en


"She had better be. I've been bending over backwards for Rumburg since my coronation."

LineNo: 14295755,

Player_Romus: She's family. Family members suppo...
en


"She's family. Family members support each other, no matter what."

LineNo: 14295857,

Player_Romus: I'm sure she wants to get Vina out...
en


"I'm sure she wants to get Vina out of there as I do."

LineNo: 14296229,

Player_Romus: This visit is just a courtesy. We'...
en


"This visit is just a courtesy. We're perfectly capable of defeating Pales on our own."

LineNo: 14296609,

Lucita Azaro: I wish I shared your optimism.
en


"I wish I shared your optimism."

LineNo: 14296711,

Lucita Azaro: As long as ATO doesn't get involve...
en


"As long as ATO doesn't get involved."

LineNo: 14296813,

Lucita Azaro: I'm sure she appreciates that.
en


"I'm sure she appreciates that."

LineNo: 14296915,

Lucita Azaro: We all do.
en


"We all do."

LineNo: 14297017,

Lucita Azaro: Beatrice's only real family in Riz...
en


"Beatrice's only real family in Rizia is Vina. But she does seem to be fond of the Princess."

LineNo: 14297119,

Lucita Azaro: You always have your family ties t...
en


"You always have your family ties to fall back on. If she still considers herself family."

LineNo: 14297221,

Player_Romus: I'm not surprised. I've done nothi...
en


"I'm not surprised. I've done nothing but alienate Rumburg since my coronation."

LineNo: 14297323,

Player_Romus: She had better be. I've been bendi...
en


"She had better be. I've been bending over backwards for Rumburg since my coronation."

LineNo: 14297425,

Player_Romus: She's family. Family members suppo...
en


"She's family. Family members support each other, no matter what."

LineNo: 14297527,

Laurento Esquibel: Yes, I have no doubt that Her Exce...
en


"Yes, I have no doubt that Her Excellency still harbors warm feelings towards you."

LineNo: 14297629,

Laurento Esquibel: You always have your family ties t...
en


"You always have your family ties to fall back on. Her Excellency was always fond of Princess Vina."

LineNo: 14297731,

Laurento Esquibel: I'm sure Her Excellency appreciate...
en


"I'm sure Her Excellency appreciates that."

LineNo: 14297833,

Player_Romus: Is that so? What did I do?
en


"Is that so? What did I do?"

LineNo: 14297935,

Laurento Esquibel: I am sure Her Excellency is eager...
en


"I am sure Her Excellency is eager to tell you in person."

LineNo: 14298037,

Player_Romus: Whatever that's worth. Rumburg has...
en


"Whatever that's worth. Rumburg hasn't been looking great internationally."

LineNo: 14298139,

Laurento Esquibel: It is still a most powerful nation...
en


"It is still a most powerful nation. And by far a more useful friend than enemy."

LineNo: 14298241,

Player_Romus: If you say so. I've been questioni...
en


"If you say so. I've been questioning the value of our so-called alliance."

LineNo: 14298343,

Lucita Azaro: It's still a very powerful country...
en


"It's still a very powerful country. By far a better friend than enemy."

LineNo: 14298445,

Narrator: The plane's door slid open. An aide...
en


The plane's door slid open. An aide informed us that everything had been cleared for our arrival.

LineNo: 14298547,

Narrator: Thornbourgh Airport, one of the big...
en


Thornbourgh Airport, one of the biggest transportation hubs in Merkopa, had been completely emptied of passengers for our visit.

LineNo: 14298927,

Narrator: She abruptly turned and regarded Lu...
en


She abruptly turned and regarded Lucita, who was standing behind me.

LineNo: 14299029,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Duchess Azaro. Your reputation pre...
en


"Duchess Azaro. Your reputation precedes you."

LineNo: 14299131,

Narrator: She abruptly turned and regarded La...
en


She abruptly turned and regarded Laurento, who was standing behind me.

LineNo: 14299233,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Mr. Esquibel. His Majesty is lucky...
en


"Mr. Esquibel. His Majesty is lucky to have retained the services of a fine statesman like yourself."

LineNo: 14299335,

Laurento Esquibel: The good fortune is all mine.
en


"The good fortune is all mine."

LineNo: 14299437,

Narrator: With a flourish, he knelt and kisse...
en


With a flourish, he knelt and kissed Beatrice's hand. She blushed slightly.

LineNo: 14299539,

Narrator: Lucita performed a graceful curtsy.
en


Lucita performed a graceful curtsy.

LineNo: 14299641,

Lucita Azaro: A pleasure to finally meet you, Yo...
en


"A pleasure to finally meet you, Your Excellency. I hope you've only heard good things."

LineNo: 14300021,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Why, of course. A noblewoman *and*...
en


"Why, of course. A noblewoman *and* a decorated military officer? You're a credit to our sex."

LineNo: 14300123,

Narrator: Her eyes traveled from Lucita to my...
en


Her eyes traveled from Lucita to myself and back. She smiled insincerely.

LineNo: 14300225,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Why, yes. Of course.
en


"Why, yes. Of course."

LineNo: 14300327,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Let's not delay. We have a full pr...
en


"Let's not delay. We have a full program of events planned at the Emerald Palace."

LineNo: 14300429,

Narrator: She cursorily introduced Lucita to...
en


She cursorily introduced Lucita to King Consort Boris and Prince Bradley. I exchanged greetings with the two men.

LineNo: 14300531,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Oh. You remember King Consort Bori...
en


"Oh. You remember King Consort Boris and Prince Bradley."

LineNo: 14300633,

Narrator: Laurento and I exchanged cursory gr...
en


Laurento and I exchanged cursory greetings with the two men.

LineNo: 14300735,

Narrator: A chauffeur opened their limousine...
en


A chauffeur opened their limousine door, and they stepped in. Queen Beatrice, Lucita and I were escorted over to a second car.

LineNo: 14300837,

Narrator: A chauffeur opened their limousine...
en


A chauffeur opened their limousine door, and they stepped in. Queen Beatrice, Laurento and I were escorted over to a second car.

LineNo: 14300939,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I hope you two don't mind the comp...
en


"I hope you two don't mind the company. We have so much to catch up on, I thought we should start right away."

LineNo: 14301065,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I hope you two don't mind the comp...
en


"I hope you two don't mind the company. We have so much to catch up on, I thought we should start right away."

LineNo: 14301183,

Player_Romus: It would be an honor to ride with...
en


"It would be an honor to ride with you."

LineNo: 14301555,

Player_Romus: Two monarchs in one car. I hope th...
en


"Two monarchs in one car. I hope there aren't any assassins about."

LineNo: 14301657,

Player_Romus: Good thinking. You never know who'...
en


"Good thinking. You never know who's listening in at the palace."

LineNo: 14301759,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Let's not delay. We have a full pr...
en


"Let's not delay. We have a full program of events planned at the Emerald Palace."

LineNo: 14301861,

Player_Romus: Must we? I was looking forward to...
en


"Must we? I was looking forward to riding in silence."

LineNo: 14301963,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Don't be silly. Where do you think...
en


"Don't be silly. Where do you think we are, Wehlen?"

LineNo: 14302343,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I was not only speaking about Pale...
en


"I was not only speaking about Pales."

LineNo: 14302445,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Splendid.
en


"Splendid."

LineNo: 14302547,

Narrator: She gave me a stern look.
en


She gave me a stern look.

LineNo: 14302745,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I am afraid we must.
en


"I am afraid we must."

LineNo: 14302847,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I assure you our security is secon...
en


"I assure you our security is second to none. But of course, one can never be too careful."

LineNo: 14302949,

Narrator: We got into the car and sat facing...
en


We got into the car and sat facing each other on leather banquettes. The engine thrummed to life, and we began moving.

LineNo: 14303051,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Frankly, given the state of things...
en


"Frankly, given the state of things between our kingdoms, I ought to leave you high and dry."

LineNo: 14303709,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Naturally, I would love to have a...
en


"Naturally, I would love to have a hand in the surrender of that self-styled Duke Reinhart."

LineNo: 14303811,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Need I remind you of your kingdom'...
en


"Need I remind you of your kingdom's broken energy promises?"

LineNo: 14303913,

Beatrice Livingston (R): What did you expect would happen w...
en


"What did you expect would happen when you undermined Rumburg by helping Wehlen in its senseless campaign against the Bluds?"

LineNo: 14304015,

Beatrice Livingston (R): What were you thinking when you to...
en


"What were you thinking when you took advantage of our embargo on Wehzek oil to begin importing it yourself?"

LineNo: 14304951,

Beatrice Livingston (R): But we share a common goal. The re...
en


"But we share a common goal. The rescue of dear Princess Vina from her Palesian captors."

LineNo: 14305053,

Beatrice Livingston (R): For the sake of my niece, I will f...
en


"For the sake of my niece, I will forgive any number of transgressions on Rizia's part."

LineNo: 14305179,

Player_Romus: Thank you, Your Excellency. That m...
en


"Thank you, Your Excellency. That means a lot to me."

LineNo: 14305281,

Player_Romus: Really? You care about Vina that m...
en


"Really? You care about Vina that much?"

LineNo: 14305383,

Player_Romus: What transgressions?
en


"What transgressions?"

LineNo: 14305485,

Beatrice Livingston (R): Do you think I'm a monster, Your M...
en


"Do you think I'm a monster, Your Majesty? She is my flesh and blood."

LineNo: 14305587,

Beatrice Livingston (R): I am not doing this for you.
en


"I am not doing this for you."

LineNo: 14305689,

Narrator: She shot me an ominous glance.
en


She shot me an ominous glance.

LineNo: 14305791,

Beatrice Livingston (R): We will get into that later. If we...
en


"We will get into that later. If we have time."

LineNo: 14305893,

Player_Romus: So you would not offer your aid if...
en
